etween the return on a portfolio of small stocks and the return on a portfolio of large stocks (SMB, small minus big); and (iii) the difference between the return on a portfolio of high-book-to-market stocks and the return on a portfolio of low-book-to-market stocks (HML, high minus low). Specifically , the expected excess return on portfolio i is, E(Ri)-Rf = bi[E(RM)-Rf] + siE(SMB) + hiE(HML), (1)},
